      "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:2:28:15",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/2/28/130",
      "text": [
        "وَمَا أَرَدْتُ ﴿إِلَّا الْإِصْلَاحَ مَا اسْتَطَعْتُ ۚ وَمَا تَوْفِيقِي إِلَّا بِاللَّـهِ ۚ عَلَيْهِ تَوَكَّلْتُ وَإِلَيْهِ أُنِيبُ﴾."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
          "“I desired naught but reform what I am able to (do); and my guidance is not but with Allāh; On Him (alone) do I rely, and unto Him (alone) do I turn.” (Qur’ān, 11:88)"
        ]
      }
    },
    "verse_translations": [
      "en.sayed-ali-raza"
    ]
